        "execSummary":  "This opinion piece challenges a dominant AI deployment assumption: that the right answer to human error is to remove human judgment from the loop through more automation or simpler interfaces. The author makes the case that organizational literacy ΓÇö not system simplicity ΓÇö is the real competitive advantage, especially as AI systems become more capable and consequential. For customer support leaders, this is directly applicable: teams that understand why AI agents make recommendations will catch more errors and build more customer trust than teams trained only to accept AI outputs. The argument carries no vendor promotion and functions as a useful counterweight to \u0027deploy and automate\u0027 narratives.",
