        "summary":  "The article traces software development\u0027s evolution from traditional coding through visual platforms, low-code, and no-code solutions toward AI-native development. It argues that AI coding agents now enable conversational interfaces where anyone can turn an idea into an app just by describing it, fundamentally changing how organizations operationalize innovation at scale.",
        "execSummary":  "This piece makes a practitioner case that we are at an inflection point where the bottleneck for building software-driven solutions has shifted from technical skill to idea quality ΓÇö anyone who can articulate a problem can now build a solution. For enterprise leaders, the implication is that domain experts in operations, support, and finance can become builders without IT mediation, which will either accelerate innovation or create sprawl depending on governance maturity. Customer support leaders specifically should consider how front-line agents and team leads might soon prototype their own AI-assisted workflows without engineering queues. The caveat is that the \u002710X\u0027 framing has been applied to multiple previous technology waves ΓÇö measured expectation-setting is warranted.",
