        "summary":  "The Linux Foundation is developing the Agent Name Service (ANS), an open standard built on DNS infrastructure to verify autonomous AI agents operating across the internet. ANS will enable secure identification of agents at scale by verifying their identity, permissions, and operational integrity, addressing governance challenges as enterprises struggle to manage rapid agentic AI deployment.",
        "execSummary":  "The Linux Foundation\u0027s Agent Name Service initiative addresses a foundational trust problem in multi-agent AI systems: if an AI agent claims authority to take an action, how do you verify it is who it says it is and that it has the permissions it claims? ANS proposes to solve this using DNS-like infrastructure, which would enable cross-vendor, cross-platform agent verification at internet scale. For enterprise architects building agentic systems ΓÇö especially in customer support where agents may hand off to other agents across vendor boundaries ΓÇö this standard could become as foundational as SSL certificates are to web security. The caveat: only 11% of tech leaders feel ready to scale agentic systems, and a new standard alone will not close that readiness gap.",
